markdown: <::FIGURE 2 Line graph showing Percent Change in Hemoglobin on the y-axis versus Infusion Period (weeks) on the x-axis. Y-axis ranges from 60 to 100. X-axis ranges from 1 to 5 weeks. Two data series are plotted: 1. Triangles (▲): SR 675 at 40 ml./Kg. (4 dogs) - Data points (approximate): (0, 100), (1, 92), (2, 88), (3, 92), (4, 90), (5, 89) 2. Circles (•): SR (1958-59) at 30-40-50 ml./Kg. (17 dogs) - Data points (approximate): (0, 100), (1, 84), (2, 77), (3, 71), (4, 72), (5, 68) Both series start at 100% hemoglobin at week 0 and show a decrease over the infusion period. The SR 675 series shows a less pronounced decrease and then stabilizes around 90%, while the SR (1958-59) series shows a more significant and continuous decrease, ending around 68% at week 5. : chart::> Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/ylwg0227
